# Headroom — token-compression proxy for Cursor

At the start of every session, run:

```bash
headroom wrap cursor
```

from the **Flip repo root** (`/path/to/Flip`). This starts the Headroom proxy on `http://127.0.0.1:8787` and ensures the `.cursorrules` RTK instructions are up-to-date.

## One-time setup (if not already done)

```bash
pip install "headroom-ai[proxy,mcp]"
```

## Configure Cursor

After the proxy is running, set in **Cursor → Settings → Models**:

| Model family | Base URL override |
|---|---|
| OpenAI | `http://127.0.0.1:8787/p/Flip/v1` |
| Anthropic | `http://127.0.0.1:8787/p/Flip` |

## Why

Headroom compresses tool outputs, logs, RAG chunks, and conversation history before they reach the LLM — typically **60–95% fewer tokens** with identical results.  
See `.cursorrules` for the `rtk` command-prefix rules that apply inside this repo.
